body:
Reading through the notes, I think an important point I was making got lost in translation - I brought up Hidalgo as a Transformer which is what @aiwalter and I were discussing last week. I was talking about algorithm assignment to be either an Annotator(Estimator) or a Transformer, based on the nature of the algorithm itself (i.e. can it make inferences on unseen data, this means to predict in the mathematical sense). 

Because both an Annotator and a Transformer are just some function `f : n x m -> n x 1` that maps to a vector, the distinction I suggested is whether or not the params depend on each row `f(θ_n)` e.g. Hidalgo, or the params are generalised `f(θ)` and we can therefore make inferences about new data e.g. k-means clustering with centre points, HMM with transition/emission matrices.
@fkiraly @miraep8
